div.p:
But this whole Digression [from ℣ 34 to 79.] has another very uncommon beauty;
for, at the same time that it arises naturally from the last consideration in the debate of the previous Question, it artfully denounces, in our entrance on the main Question, the principal topics intended to be employed for the dilucidation of it, namely AVA
RICE, PROFUSION, and PUBLIC CORRUPTION.
